.TH CLIPBOARD\-FUNCTIONALITY 1 "2026\-02\-25" "dotfiles" "Clipboard Functionality Manual"
.SH NAME
clipboard\-functionality \- persistent clipboard history system for sway/waybar
.SH DESCRIPTION
The clipboard functionality provides a persistent, searchable clipboard history
manager for a sway/Wayland desktop environment.
.PP
Every clipboard change is captured, normalized (UTF\-16 LE is automatically
converted to UTF\-8 so browser\-copied URLs always appear clean), and stored
in a local SQLite database.
A waybar icon reflects the history size and provides click\-based access to the
history browser.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B $mod+Shift+p
Opens the interactive clipboard history browser (rofi).
.RS
.TP
.B Enter
Copy selected item back to the clipboard.
.TP
.B Delete
Remove selected item from history (stays open for next action).
.TP
.B Escape
Close the picker without copying.
.RE
.TP
.B Waybar left\-click
Opens the clipboard history browser.
.TP
.B Waybar right\-click
Opens a deletion picker (remove individual items).
.TP
.B Waybar middle\-click
Clears the entire clipboard history.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/clipboard\-manager.sh
Interactive history browser (rofi UI).
Entry point for keyboard and waybar interactions.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/clipboard\-utf16\-filter.py
Storage middleware.
Converts UTF\-16 LE clipboard data (e.g. URLs copied from Brave) to UTF\-8
before handing off to cliphist store.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/clipboard\-store\-daemon.sh
Daemon launcher for the storage pipeline.
Kills any existing
.B wl\-paste \-\-watch clipboard\-utf16\-filter.py
instance then starts a fresh one.
Called by
.B exec_always $cliphist_store
in
.IR 99\-autostart\-applications.conf .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/clipboard\-watch\-daemon.sh
Daemon launcher for the waybar refresh signal.
Kills any existing
.B wl\-paste \-\-watch waybar\-signal clipboard
instance then starts a fresh one.
Called by
.B exec_always $cliphist_watch
in
.IR 99\-autostart\-applications.conf .
.TP
.I ~/.config/rofi/themes/coffee\-metal
Rofi theme for the clipboard picker and deletion dialogs.
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
Waybar module definition
.RI ( custom/clipboard ,
signal\ 9).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/autostart
Daemon variable definitions:
.BR $cliphist_store ", " $cliphist_watch ", " $clip\-persist .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/01\-definitions.conf
User\-facing variable definitions:
.BR $clipboard ", " $clipboard\-del .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config.d/99\-autostart\-applications.conf
Launches the three clipboard daemons at sway startup.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/shutdown
Purges clipboard history on logout/shutdown/reboot (if configured).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/cliphist/db
SQLite database storing clipboard history (managed by cliphist).
.SH PROGRAMS
The following programs must be installed for this functionality to work:
.TP
.B cliphist
Clipboard history backend.
Stores and retrieves entries from the SQLite database.
.TP
.B wl\-paste
Wayland clipboard reader.
Used in
.B \-\-watch
mode to monitor clipboard changes.
.TP
.B wl\-copy
Wayland clipboard writer.
Restores a selected history entry to the active clipboard.
.TP
.B wl\-clip\-persist
Keeps clipboard data alive after the source application closes,
preventing "clipboard lost on window close".
.TP
.B waybar\-signal
IPC utility.
Sends POSIX signal RTMIN+9 to waybar to refresh the clipboard module.
.TP
.B rofi
Launcher used as the picker UI for history browsing and deletion.
.SH DAEMONS
Three background processes run continuously,
all started by
.I 99\-autostart\-applications.conf
at sway startup:
.TP
.B wl\-paste \-\-watch clipboard\-utf16\-filter.py
Monitors the Wayland clipboard.
On each change, pipes the raw data through the UTF\-16 filter to
.BR "cliphist store" .
Started via
.B $cliphist_store
in autostart.
.TP
.B wl\-paste \-\-watch waybar\-signal\ clipboard
Monitors the Wayland clipboard.
On each change, signals waybar to refresh the clipboard icon and tooltip.
Started via
.B $cliphist_watch
in autostart.
.TP
.B wl\-clip\-persist \-\-clipboard regular ...
Persists clipboard data after the source application closes.
Started via
.B $clip\-persist
in autostart
.RI ( exec_always ,
so it restarts on sway reload).
.SH STORAGE
Clipboard history is stored in
.IR ~/.cache/cliphist/db
(SQLite format, managed by cliphist).
.PP
Maximum items: 750 (cliphist default).
.PP
The database is purged automatically on logout, shutdown, and reboot if the
variable
.B $purge_cliphist_logout
is set to
.I true
in your sway configuration.
.PP
It can also be cleared manually via middle\-click on the waybar clipboard icon,
or by running:
.PP
.RS
.B rm \-f ~/.cache/cliphist/db
.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.B Max history size
Pass
.B \-max\-items <n>
to
.B cliphist store
by editing
.B $cliphist_store
in
.IR ~/.config/sway/autostart .
.TP
.B Purge on logout
Set
.B $purge_cliphist_logout
to
.I true
in your sway config.
.TP
.B Picker theme
Edit
.I ~/.config/rofi/themes/coffee\-metal
to change the picker appearance.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cliphist (1),
.BR wl\-paste (1),
.BR wl\-copy (1),
.BR wl\-clip\-persist (1),
.BR rofi (1),
.BR waybar (5)
